OL,3,CHow Mandelson flunked the vetting but
OL,4,Cstill became US ambassador
OL,6,FAnyone appointed to a job where they
OL,7,Fwill have access to government
OL,8,Fsecrets, or have the kind of influence
OL,9,Fpotentially valuable to the UK's
OL,10,Fenemies, has to undergo what's called
OL,11,Fdeveloped vetting before getting the
OL,12,Fjob.
OL,14,FThis involves being locked in a room
OL,15,Fwith an anonymous official, often an
OL,16,Ferstwhile spook, and being asked
OL,17,Fimpertinent and embarrassing questions.
OL,19,FOne former senior official tells me
OL,20,Fthat in his vetting interview, he had
OL,21,Fto reveal the porn websites he uses.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
